===Noun===
'''phyllo'''

# A [[dough]] used in thin layers to make [[pastries]], originating in [[Mediterranean]] [[cuisine]].  Versions of phyllo can also be used as crusts for [[pies]] or [[casseroles]].  Phyllo is used in many [[Middle Eastern]] cuisines for example the [[famous]] [[baklava]].

